title: Spruce Forest
description: Photogrammetry rocks, plants and trees, paintable landscape automaterial, realistic wind system
longDescription:
Realistic and optimized Spruce Forest with photoscanned assets, realistic wind system and paintable landscape automaterial. Easy to customize with material instances and Global Material Parameter Collection.


Demo Level Walk (UE4)

Cinematic (UE5)

HQ Screenshots
technicalDetails:
* To use all the features from the demo level (changing day and night, seasons, etc.), then you need to add an input - DefaultInput (Project Settings -> Input -> Import or copy and replace this file in the config folder)

**Â Make sure you have the Niagara plugin enabled to use rain, falling leaves and snow particles


Features:


  • Trees: 8 big (+ 4 small)
  • Rocks: 10 (+6 small rocks for ground cover)
  • Plants: 10
  • Paintable automated landscape material with procedural plants and rocks
  • Wind system
  • 3 Niagara particles systems (snow, rain and falling leaves)
  • Procedural Winter and Autumn
  • Procedural puddles
  • Water material
  • Interactive foliage
  • Road and Path spline meshes


Number of Unique Meshes: 55

Collision: Yes

Vertex Count: 30-1000 (Plants), 1000-2000 (Logs, Stumps), 1000-2000 (Rocks), ~5000 (Trees, LOD0)

LODs: 1-3 levels (automatically generated) + Billboards for all trees and some plants

Number of Materials and Material Instances: 4 Master Materials (Meshes, Landscape, Water, Particles), 41 Material Instances

Number of Textures: 97

Texture Resolutions: 4096x4096

Supported Development Platforms:

Windows: Yes

Mac: No
